pulses.name: Malicious IP's pulled from Modem logs - But wait, there's more, more more! Was able to pilfer a full Ave Maria RAT stack from ips
pulses.description: These are all ips pulled from my Modem that have hit as malicious either through criminalip.io or OTX. T. I was fortunate enough OTX was able to pull about 20 samples of .NET malware (showing as unclassified) and previously had not been in at least the public facing database. The stats are all over the plac; with some having samples as late as an hour ago. And some being last uploaded around 10-12 months ago. Compilation dates are around the same. This seems to be an active cluster emanating out of the CCP with one or two of the files looking like their some sort of Chinese browser modified for malicious purposes and actively communicating with a c2.
